main event: An unidentified flying object was observed for 25-30 minutes on January 15, 1965.
interesting points: The observation was made in Long Beach, Mississippi,The conclusion identified the object as a possible aircraft helicopter,Two objects were reported during the sighting,The altitude of the objects was approximately 1000 feet,According to the report, there was no physical evidence or photographs of the sighting.
witness description: no witnesses identified in the report
